The so-called Dactylie Pentameter is really only a modification of the hexameter. Instead of a dactyl or spondee in the third foot it has one aecented long syllable followed by diaeresis, and instead of a spondee or a trochee in the sixth foot one aecented syllable either long or short. Spondees may be substituted for dactyls in the first two · feet only.
